(firstQuint)Characteristics and Outcomes of Childhood Moyamoya in the UK.

 The study ahs 3 components: 1.

 Patient identification via the British Paediatric Surveillance Unit, and the 21 collaborating centres 2.

 Record review/patient interview to determine clinical features & outcomes 3.

 Centralised review of imaging data to ascertain radiological phenotypes.

 Characteristics and Outcomes of Childhood Moyamoya in the UK@highlight

This is a study to ascertain the number of children with moyamoya in the UK, their presenting features, clinical course and outcomes.

